$MSTR is the undisputed king of #Bitcoin corporate treasuries. There is no second best.

But could there be a second best someday?

Possibly, but there is an enormous hurdle to overcome, and it's not a financial problem, but a marketing problem. Let me explain.

Positioning

In their seminal marketing book of the same name, Al Ries and Jack Trout introduced the concept of "Positioning."

Positioning is essentially the way a product or brand differentiates itself from competitors.

The textbook example of positioning is Coca-Cola vs. Pepsi. Coke positions itself as the original cola, whereas Pepsi is the "challenger" and its marketing emphasizes youthful energy, excitement, and rebellion.

MicroStrategy's positioning is "leveraged bitcoin." When you buy MicroStrategy stock, you're buying Michael Saylor's unwavering commitment to acquiring as much Bitcoin as possible as quickly as possible.

Your decision to buy $MSTR might be influenced by charts and numbers, but the mere numeric case for returns is not fundamentally what drives fandom of the company.

There is no significant number two player. There is no Pepsi to MicroStrategy's Coke.

First Mover Advantage

Typically, the first product in a category dominates the category. It can even become synonymous with the category. Think of Kleenex, Band-Aids, and Velcro.

Likewise, we talk about any company starting a Bitcoin treasury today as "running the MicroStrategy playbook."

#MetaPlanet has been literally dubbed "The MicroStrategy of Japan." 

Positioning Against the Leader

This is only the beginning of the positioning problems for new adopters of Bitcoin treasuries.

Even before we get to their market share, it's not clear what "mindshare" they will occupy. "Me too" is not a strong foundation to build on.

Compounding the problem, the way I see investment cases presented for these companies often looks more like special situation investing with a one-time pop rather than an enduring value proposition.

Typical market structure and human mind space converges on only 3 major brands in a product category.

For major second and third place players in the Bitcoin corporate treasury space to emerge, companies will not only need to successfully execute strategies for acquiring enough bitcoin to secure their rankings, but also clearly differentiate their positioning.

Possible Positioning Strategies

If MicroStrategy is "leveraged bitcoin," perhaps another company could be "3x leveraged bitcoin."

There would be practical problems making "3x leveraged bitcoin" positioning a reality, but the general principle is that there needs to be a clear rationale why you would allocate part of your portfolio to the other stock in order for it to capture market share.

I.e., if you want leveraged Bitcoin buy $MSTR, if you want 3x leveraged Bitcoin buy stock XYZ.

Of current companies implementing Bitcoin treasuries, MetaPlanet has the strongest positioning. Even though "The MicroStrategy of Japan" has a "me too" ring to it, it still establishes a clear niche in Japan that makes sense because of the geographical practicalities of investing.

Bullish on Bitcoin Corporate Treasuries

Despite challenges with positioning, I am enormously bullish on the potential for Bitcoin as a treasury asset to add value for companies and investors.

It's already too late for any company to catch up with MicroStrategy for the number one spot, but number two and three are still up for grabs.

I'm massively rooting for companies like $SMLR to carve out their own niche in the space.

That said, not every company needs to popularize itself as a Bitcoin proxy in order to benefit from holding Bitcoin in its treasury. There is no second best treasury asset.

if microstrategy is "leveraged bitcoin," perhaps another company could be "3x leveraged bitcoin."

there would be practical problems making "3x leveraged bitcoin" positioning a reality, but the general principle is that there needs to be a clear rationale why you would allocate part of your portfolio to the other stock in order for it to capture market share.

i.e., if you want leveraged bitcoin buy $mstr, if you want 3x leveraged bitcoin buy stock xyz.

of current companies implementing bitcoin treasuries, metaplanet has the strongest positioning. even though "the microstrategy of japan" has a "me too" ring to it, it still establishes a clear niche in japan that makes sense because of the geographical practicalities of investing.

bullish on bitcoin corporate treasuries

despite challenges with positioning, i am enormously bullish on the potential for bitcoin as a treasury asset to add value for companies and investors.

it's already too late for any company to catch up with microstrategy for the number one spot, but number two and three are still up for grabs.

i'm massively rooting for companies like $smlr to carve out their own niche in the space.

that said, not every company needs to popularize itself as a bitcoin proxy in order to benefit from holding bitcoin in its treasury. there is no second best treasury asset.

I am 95% confident we have bottomed here at $52.5k.
 
And 95% confident that we will not see anywhere near $44k whatsoever.
 
The USDT Dominance chart is one of the most reliable charts to predict Bitcoin tops and reversals.

Currently, USDT Dominance is at levels not seen since the bear market when Bitcoin was trading at $27k.
 
The chart is also at very key resistance, touching levels that have only existed within bear markets.
 
We have also over a 30% plus move to the downside on USDT Dominance until it reaches the trend line that has predicted every Bitcoin top with 100% accuracy.
 
This adds a serious amount of confluence to the bottoming pattern that Bitcoin is printing.
 
For Bitcoin to reach $44k USDT Dominance would have to enter areas that are only seen in true bear markets.
 
This would break HTF structure on both charts, and we would actually see much lower than $44k in the end.
 
If you‚Äôre wishing for $44k, you are actually wishing for $30k.
 
There is of course a probability that USDT.D breaks higher, but it is very small imo.

Investing is a game of probabilities, and based on the evidence of the entire market situation we are in, the probability is greatly weighted to the upside from where I look.

Let's see how the rest of the month plays out.

I'm excited to dive into the innovative world of @MantaNetwork, a blockchain ecosystem revolutionizing the way we approach zero knowledge (ZK) applications. 

With two primary networks, #MantaPacific and #MantaAtlantic, this platform is making waves in the crypto space.

Manta Pacific, built on Ethereum, offers a Layer 2 solution for EVM-native ZK applications, providing scalability and low gas fees. Meanwhile, Manta Atlantic, on Polkadot, boasts the fastest ZK chain, introducing groundbreaking concepts like programmable identities via zkSBTs.

What sets Manta Network apart?

Privacy: Enhanced user data protection through ZK proofs
Interoperability: Seamless interaction with other blockchains, amplifying utility across ecosystems
Modularity: Support for independent and collaborative functionalities, ideal for various applications from DeFi to identity verification

Recent developments showcase Manta Network's growing momentum:

- Significant transaction volumes and project integrations, demonstrating active usage and ecosystem growth
- Partnerships and integrations, like with Router Protocol for cross-chain transfers, expanding interoperability

The $MANTA token plays a crucial role in governance, staking, and transaction fees across both networks, with a strategic distribution model to incentivize ecosystem growth and user engagement.

Join me in exploring the vast potential of Manta Network, where innovation meets functionality. #MantaNeverStops"

cleaned_data.original_text:
Lets get #PulseChain on the same playing field,

You are going to want to bookmark this tweet so you can come back to it later.

It's come to my attention there are many in the community who are new to Crypto and don't really understand how easy things are, while others make you believe they are hard to do and are more in the know, they aren't.

I'm going to show you how to track wallets, token prices, set up alerts, copy trading, token sniping, how to find new token launches etc and tell you the basic of what you need to know.

This is long from, so people can come back to it as they need. Everything in this thread is user friendly and ANYONE can use them. They require 0 skill set or knowledge of code etc.

- Lets start with tracking wallets, token prices, buys and sells, liquidity pools etc with the Etherdrops bot. This bot can also be used to track things such as validator addresses which is how in rooms people like myself track $'s being bridged over.

First up you need Telegram, most bots run through telegram, IF you use TG, make sure you go into settings and turn off the default allowing people to add you to rooms, if you don't you will always be added into rooms with scams. Learn how to protect yourself, TG is known for major scams.

This bot has supported PulseChain since it pretty much launched. This is how we know the movements of wallets such as the OA before everyone, track known whales in the community, the PulseBridge etc. 

This bot is great for people who also want to track things like liquidity in pairs being thinned or removed, hackers wallets (all you have to do is paste a wallet and it starts tracking, takes 2 second), tokens prices i.e if you wanted to track CST or PXDC stablecoins on PulseChain say for -10% moves to arb and redeem etc

Many in the community will use this bot to track known sellers, buyers, hacker wallets, large ecosystem holders etc.

This bot is fully customisable to, you can choose % token price increase and decrease, size of buys or txns it tracks etc. Making it the ultimate tracking bot for PulseChain. (not the only one but IMO the best)

- Next up we have bots for sniping, copy trading and limit orders with Prodigy bot. 

This bot has had full PulseChain support for many months now. But this does involve some explaining.

- Sniping - Understand this isn't something that happens in the first 5 minutes of launch, that is just people market buying and being lucky getting in early (they usually pay CRAZY high gas fees in comparison to you to assure their txns get in first, so if you want to buy in early learn how to increase your gas settings), sniping happens in the first block. 99% of the time this is not 'insiders' but market participants taking advantage of a dumb dev or founder. 

If you post the contract address before deploying the liquidity you will 100% be snipped. This is nothing new, many of you need to look at SOL, they have great websites like Photon and realise this is apart of crypto. Sniping is the reflection of a stupid deployer you probs shouldn't be supporting because they already show lack of experience. All launches should be from fresh wallets as you seen above, known wallets and founders etc are already being tracked, deploy a token contract you will be snipped.

The sniping itself is easy, Prodigy bot is literally just paste an address, snipe ready. It has settings like anti rug etc to protect you. 

- Copy trading, people who are already tracking wallets use this bot regularly. Lets use SOL as an example here because it has high meme activity, if you actively watch the order books and see a wallet that makes great trades, gets in early and has a high win rate, instead of just 'tracking' their wallet on Etherdrops you can set up Prodigy to literally just copy their trades for you.

See how these things are very simple? You just don't know the tools.

- Limit orders, Prodigy bot is used for limit orders, while PulseChain doesn't have too many limit order options, but you see wicks as if people have limit orders set, some of those are coming from this bot on TG. This bot can be set up to buy and sell coins at any $ or % target you set. 

If you buy in early to a meme coin for example and are a profit taking maxi you can set this bot up to sell half your bags every 100%+ move etc. So while it is limit orders it is also a bot for profit taking etc.

- It's faster than humans, what do I mean by that? If you are anticipating a new token launch, if you are looking to buy new tokens fast, you can set this bot up to buy X amount (whatever you choose) on paste, you can even set high gas settings to assure your txn goes through. This bot more times than not will be faster than humans manually trying to copy paste and push the txn through, as it can do it in fraction of a second at predetermined settings you have made. No inputing values etc.

Now is a good time to note, take caution when using this bot, you are given your own private key, your own seed etc, but NEVER store money on a TG bot, if you are using it send only what you want to use at the time, and never store tokens on it, always send them back to your wallet when you are done.

In saying all that, this bot can make users a lot of money and is worth checking out and learning how to use the tools avaiable to you. 

- Next up we have DEXtools live new pairs, where do people find new token launches?

DEXtools is great to watch new token launches, it gives you all the information needed like CA, where it was launched, liquidity amount it launched with, does it have a website, logo etc. You soon can soon work out fast what's jeet and what isn't. But be cautious that isn't a clear indication of if it's a scam or not. If you check out SOL on DEXtools or Photon (cool SOL tool) you will see 99% are rugs. Learn the meme game before you go chasing and losing money faster than in a casino.

As always, nothing I have said in this thread is advice or am I in no way telling you do do any of these thing. Always proceed with caution, do your own research and learn about these things first, risks etc.

You think there are 'advanced' players, really they have just been here for more than one cycle, so they know about more tools available than you. You need 0 skills to do any of these things. You only need to DYOR. Check websites, triple check them, remember this place is FULL of scams, scam links etc.

Have fun learning how to up your game and be on the same level. Bull market is here and you know we are all going to make money! Have fun, stay safe.

Or maybe you‚Äôre a Bitcoiner and you love the fact that BTC is legal tender here.

As a solo mom with a child, my favorite thing is how safe I feel living here. 

I got the recommendation from several family members that to stay safe in El salvador I just needed to stay out of the bad areas.  

Thanks to @nayibbukele there are no bad areas

Both tourists and locals can feel safe to explore and get lost and not fear ending up in the wrong place.  

If your a woman, if you‚Äôve ever traveled. I bet you‚Äôve never felt 100% safe in every area. Unless of course you‚Äôve traveled here to El Salvador.

The USA deserves a president that will fight for the safety of its people and build a country where woman can feel safe to travel alone.

üìçKey features of this source code release:
üî∏ brc-20 on Fractal with specific rules (detailing differences from Bitcoin mainnet rules)
üî∏ Full event stream, including the swap module (beneficial for DeFi projects utilizing #PizzaSwap liquidity)

üîóGitHub link:
https://t.co/PaEGZgM5xA

(Note: For performance reasons, this is an isolated branch specifically for brc-20.)

Building on the open-source implementations for Ordinals, brc-20, and other protocols, we will continue to release additional protocol implementations for Fractal, like the Runes protocol indexing component, to gradually create a developer-friendly source code framework.‚ú®

Stay tuned for more updates!

Now Coinbase wants a piece of that, too. Just remember, in spite of Coinbase launching wrapped Bitcoin on Ethereum and Base, it's not offering the same ecosystem and opportunities like #Flarenetwork. Ethereum is just a no-go due to extreme high gas.

cleaned_data.original_text: In her latest podcast, Hawk Tuah discussed why she believes Ethereum is inferior to Bitcoin and destined to fail. She argued that Ethereum's frequent network upgrades and the shift to Ethereum 2.0 introduce significant instability and unpredictability, unlike Bitcoin's consistent and secure protocol. Tuah highlighted Ethereum's scalability issues, claiming that despite its smart contract functionality, the network congestion and high gas fees make it less practical for everyday transactions compared to Bitcoin's growing Lightning Network. She also pointed out the centralization risks with Ethereum's proof-of-stake model, suggesting it undermines the decentralized ethos more than Bitcoin's proof-of-work. Furthermore, she critiqued Ethereum's monetary policy, noting that its ever-changing supply could not compete with Bitcoin's fixed supply cap, which she sees as a true store of value akin to digital gold. Lastly, Tuah mentioned the cultural and market perception, where Bitcoin is often viewed as the primary entry point into crypto investments, potentially overshadowing Ethereum's technological advancements and utility in the long run.

CULTURAL FOUNDATION 

I‚Äôve mentioned a few times I studied finance at uni, but it was also a double degree with civil engineering

Majority of it's irrelevant to crypto but one of the biggest analogies from those days is the importance of a strong foundation

A big percentage of material and work that goes into roads, bridges and buildings is beneath the surface

Nobody can see any of this work, but without a solid foundation they‚Äôre almost certain to fail

And I believe projects and communities are very similar

Majority of work that goes into building a successful project and community goes unseen

But it‚Äôs this core foundation that gives projects strength to survive long term

No single pillar carries the entire load

If one fails, others are their to compensate

It‚Äôs one of the things I‚Äôve been most proud of over the last six months within our community

A projects culture shouldn‚Äôt rely on a single person

Yes the founders should have a big impact, they set the tone and lead the way

But when you‚Äôre investing in something on Bitcoin you want it to have as much decentralization as possible, leaders included, eliminate the key man risk

The art, culture and community should be the foundation

And this takes time, I would say years to be sustainable but that‚Äôs the ultimate goal

And don‚Äôt worry, I‚Äôm not going anywhere, this is my life and I love everything about it but I never want Fomojis to be all about me

We‚Äôre always gonna innovate and experiment to add as much value as possible but it should be about every single holder!

YOU are all the foundation, and we build together!

The community has continued to step up even in the most down periods over the last six months and now it's time to get to the next level

We came out last bear stronger and will come out of this one even stronger again!
